@startuml 11_attribute_restriction_component
title Attribute Level Security (ALS) Component Diagram

skinparam componentStyle uml2

package "Host Laravel Application" {
    [User Model] <<Eloquent>>
    [Role Model] <<Eloquent>>
    
    interface "DynamicReportSubject" as IDRS
    
    [User Model] .up.|> IDRS : implements
    note right of [User Model]
      getDynamicReportSubjects()
      returns [User, Role1, Role2]
    end note
}

package "Nisalatp\\DynamicReportGenerator" {
    
    component "ReportMaker (Engine)" as Engine
    component "Security Validator" as Validator
    
    [AttributeRestriction] <<Eloquent Model>>
    database "dynamic_attribute_restrictions" as DB_Table
    
    [AttributeRestriction] ..> DB_Table : reads/writes
}

[User Model] --> Engine : Executing Context (auth()->user())

Engine --> IDRS : Resolves active subjects
Engine --> [AttributeRestriction] : Queries rules for active subjects

Engine *-- Validator : delegates AST checks
Validator --> Engine : throws ReportMakerSecurityException\n(if blocked attribute used in calculations)

note bottom of Engine
  Builds SQL Builder:
  - Masks output if rule is 'masked'
  - Injects '###' if rule is 'blocked'
end note

@enduml
